    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER HEAD REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean valve faces and seats with a suitable cleaning solvent to remove all dirt or
                    foreign material. Blow dry all new and used components using filtered compressed air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thoroughly clean all valve guides, prior to valve installation, as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Coat a nylon brush with soap and water as shown in
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150458">4.58</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Brush must have a slightly larger diameter than the I.D. of the valve guide.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Insert brush into valve guide bore and clean with a turning motion to insure removal
                        of any deposits.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Dry with filtered compressed air.</para>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">PERFORM VALVE GUIDE BORE CLEANING ON:</emph>
                    </para>
                    <seqlist style="arabic">
                        <item>
                            <para>NEW SERVICE VALVE GUIDES.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>VALVE GUIDES INSTALLED IN NEW SERVICE CYLINDER HEADS (LESS VALVES).</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>VALVE GUIDES PRESENTLY INSTALLED IN CYLINDER HEAD, WHICH MEET BORE SPECIFICATIONS.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the valve stem with clean engine oil and insert the valve into the valve
                    guide.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">For Engines Built After S/N 594857</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the stem seal assembly over the valve and valve guide and against the cylinder
                    head as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150459">4.59</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve spring over the stem seal assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rotator assembly over the valve spring. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150460">4.60</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compress the valve spring and install the spring locks as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150461">4.61</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150458" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14688" filename="../figcg1/cg14688.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.58. Clean Valve Guide Bores.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150459" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14712" filename="../figcg1/cg14712.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.59. Install Stem Seal Assembly.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150460" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14691" filename="../figcg1/cg14691.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.60. Install Valve Spring and Rotator.</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">For Engines Built Before S/N 594858</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Snap the plastic oil shield into the valve rotator as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150462">4.62</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>ON EARLY MODELS, EQUIPPED WITH THE NYLON OIL SHIELD, THE SHIELD MUST BE SNAPPED INTO THE
                            ROTATOR (FIGURE
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150461">4.61</hotlnk>). IF NOT PROPERLY INSTALLED, EXCESSIVE LUBE OIL
                            CONSUMPTION COULD OCCUR.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150461" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12057" filename="../figcg1/cg12057.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.61. Compress Springs and Install Spring Locks.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150462" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12054" filename="../figcg1/cg12054.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.62. Assemble Rotator and Oil Shield (Used Prior to S/N 594858).</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the spring seat over the valve stem and guide. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150407.xml" xrefid="ef4150463">4.63</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve spring and rotator with oil shield. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150407.xml" xrefid="ef4150464">4.64</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compress the valve spring and install the spring locks as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150461">4.61</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
